description.en: The issue number of the referenced Gazette (to find this from the date, consult WP:London Gazette Index)
The publication date of the referenced Gazette. This should be in the format day month year.
The page of the referenced Gazette on which the citation is found - Except when citing a whole issue, for example for the Birthday Honours List.
The page range of the reference Gazette in the form number–number where the two page numbers are separated by a ndash

For a link in a supplement to a Gazette - To correctly format the URL to link to a page in a Gazette supplement, set this parameter to the number of the supplement (typically, supp=1); otherwise omit it.
Some supplements are accessed without an alteration to the standard ULR in which case use this parameter and not the supp parameter.
To display the name of the Gazette without a wikilink (e.g. if there are multiple uses of the template on the same page, allow the link on the first but disable the rest)

Either |city=e for Edinburgh Gazette, |city=b for Belfast Gazette or |city=o for the Oxford Gazette as the first 23 issues of the London Gazette were titled. The city names may also be spelt out in full if you prefer, e.g. |city=Edinburgh
Appends a quote to the end of the template.
Used in conjunction with the harv template. It can be altered to any value
Setting ''mode=cs2'' changes the style to ensure consistency with Citation style 2, as produced by the Citation template
To remove the final period, or change it to any other character — now semi-redundant use the mode parameter instead.

This template is used to provide references to pages in the London Gazette online archive website. The London Gazette is the official newspaper of the British government for England and Wales in which all official notices are published. The template is provided to simplify the entering of addresses. An index by number/date (i.e. if you know the number or date you can find the document) is at WP:London Gazette Index.

The template may also be used to provide references to pages in the of the Edinburgh Gazette online archives and to Belfast Gazette online archives.

Template:Cite journal.description: This template formats a citation to an article in a magazine or journal, using the provided source information (e.g. journal name, author, title, issue, URL) and various formatting options.

url.label: URL
url.description: The URL of the online location where the text of the publication can be found. Requires schemes of the type "http://..." or maybe even the  protocol relative scheme "//..."

title.label: Title
title.description: The title of the article; can be wikilinked to an existing Wikipedia article or url may be used to add an external link, but not both. Displays in quotes.

last.label: Last name
last.description: The surname of the author; don't wikilink, use 'authorlink'; can suffix with a numeral to add additional authors

first.label: First name
first.description: Given or first name, middle names, or initials of the author; don't wikilink, use 'authorlink'; can suffix with a numeral to add additional authors

last2.label: Last name 2
last2.description: The surname of the second author; don't wikilink, use 'authorlink2'.

first2.label: First name 2
first2.description: Given or first name, middle names, or initials of the second author; don't wikilink.

date.label: Source date
date.description: Date of the source; do not wikilink. As listed in the publication

journal.label: Journal
journal.description: Name of the source journal; may be wikilinked; displays in italics; alias of 'work'

publisher.label: Publisher
publisher.description: Name of the publisher; displays after title

issue.label: Issue
issue.description: Issue identifier when the source is part of a series that is published periodically

doi-broken-date.label: DOI broken date
doi-broken-date.description: The date that the DOI was determined to be broken

others.label: Others
others.description: Used to record other contributions to the work, such as 'Illustrated by John Smith' or 'Translated by John Smith'

year.label: Year of publication
year.description: Year of the source being referenced; recommended only when date parameter format is YYYY-MM-DD and a CITEREF disambiguator is needed

orig-year.label: Original year
orig-year.description: Original year of publication; provide specifics

editor-last.label: Editor last name
editor-last.description: The surname of the editor; don't wikilink, use 'editor-link'; can suffix with a numeral to add additional editors; alias of 'editor1-last', 'editor'

editor-first.label: Editor first name
editor-first.description: Given or first name, middle names, or initials of the editor; don't wikilink, use 'editor-link'; can suffix with a numeral to add additional editors; alias of 'editor1-first'

editor-link.label: Editor link
editor-link.description: Title of existing Wikipedia article about the editor; can suffix with a numeral to add additional editors; alias of 'editor1-link'

series.label: Series
series.description: Series identifier when the source is part of a series, such as a book series or a journal; alias of 'version'

location.label: Location of publication
location.description: Geographical place of publication; usually not wikilinked; omit when the publication name includes place; alias of 'place'

publication-place.label: Place of publication
publication-place.description: Publication place shows after title; if 'place' or 'location' are also given, they are displayed before the title prefixed with 'written at'

publication-date.label: Publication date
publication-date.description: Date of publication when different from the date the work was written; do not wikilink

edition.label: Edition
edition.description: When the publication has more than one edition; for example: '2nd', 'Revised' etc.; suffixed with ' ed.'

volume.label: Volume
volume.description: For one publication published in several volumes

page.label: Page
page.description: Page in the source that supports the content; displays after 'p.'

pages.label: Pages
pages.description: Pages in the source that support the content (not an indication of the number of pages in the source; displays after 'pp.'

nopp.label: No pp
nopp.description: Set to 'y' to suppress the 'p.' or 'pp.' display with 'page' or 'pages' when inappropriate (such as 'Front cover')

at.label: At
at.description: May be used instead of 'page' or 'pages' where a page number is inappropriate or insufficient

language.label: Language
language.description: The language in which the source is written, if not English; use the full language name; do not use icons or templates

script-title.label: Script title
script-title.description: For titles in languages that do not use a Latin-based alphabet (Arabic, Chinese, Cyrillic, Greek, Hebrew, Japanese, Korean, Vietnamese, etc). Prefix with two-character ISO639-1 language code followed by a colon. For Japanese use: |script-title=ja:...

trans-title.label: Translated title
trans-title.description: An English language title, if the source cited is in a foreign language; 'language' is recommended

type.label: Type
type.description: Additional information about the media type of the source; format in sentence case

format.label: Format
format.description: Format of the work referred to by 'url' ('url' is required when using 'format'); examples: PDF, DOC, XLS; do not specify HTML

arxiv.label: arXiv identifier
arxiv.description: An identifier for arXive electronic preprints of scientific papers

asin-tld.label: ASIN TLD
asin-tld.description: ASIN top-level domain for Amazon sites other than the US

citeseerx.label: CiteSeerX
citeseerx.description: CiteSeerX identifier; found after the 'doi=' query parameter

isbn.label: ISBN
isbn.description: International Standard Book Number; use the 13-digit ISBN where possible

issn.label: ISSN
issn.description: International Standard Serial Number (print); 8 characters; usually split into two groups of four using a hyphen

eissn.label: eISSN
eissn.description: International Standard Serial Number (online); 8 characters; usually split into two groups of four using a hyphen

jfm.label: jfm code
jfm.description: Jahrbuch über die Fortschritte der Mathematik classification code

osti.label: OSTI
osti.description: Office of Scientific and Technical Information identifier

id.label: id
id.description: A unique identifier used where none of the specialized ones are applicable

quote.label: Quote
quote.description: Relevant text quoted from the source; displays last, enclosed in quotes; needs to include terminating punctuation

ref.label: Ref
ref.description: An anchor identifier; can be made the target of wikilinks to full references; special value 'harv' generates an anchor suitable for the harv and sfn templates

separator.label: Separator
separator.description: The punctuation used to separate lists of authors, editors, etc.; a space must be encoded as   to suppress use reserved keyword 'none'

postscript.label: Postscript
postscript.description: The closing punctuation for the citation; ignored if 'quote' is defined; to suppress use reserved keyword 'none'
